<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> give someone the freedom of the city • give someone the freedom of the world</xh5><p> <i>give someone the freedom of the city</i>—confer upon a person honorary citizenship of a city: Harrison was <u>given the freedom of the city</u> and was the guest of honor at the London Rotary Club.</p><p> <i>give someone the freedom of the world</i>—<i>(sl.)</i> dismiss smb. from employment: I used to work for IBM, but one day they called me in and <u>gave me the freedom of the world</u>, so now I have my own business.</p> </entry>
